## Vercel Speed Insights Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Next.js App Router project.

### Changes Made:

1. **Package Installation**
   - Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` v2.0.0 using pnpm
   - Updated `package.json` to include the new dependency
   - Generated `pnpm-lock.yaml` with updated dependencies

2. **Code Integration**
   - Modified `src/app/layout.tsx` to import and include the SpeedInsights component
   - Added `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
   - Placed `<SpeedInsights />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag, after the existing content

### Implementation Details:

Following the official Vercel documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart), I implemented the recommended setup for Next.js App Router (v13.5+):

- The SpeedInsights component was added to the root layout file as per Next.js App Router best practices
- The component is placed at the end of the body to ensure it doesn't interfere with initial page rendering
- The import uses the framework-specific path `@vercel/speed-insights/next` for optimal integration

### Verification:

- ✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
- ✅ TypeScript compilation passed
- ✅ No linting errors introduced in layout.tsx
- ✅ All existing functionality preserved

### Files Modified:

- `package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `src/app/layout.tsx` - Integrated SpeedInsights component
- `pnpm-lock.yaml` - Updated lockfile with new dependencies

The Speed Insights feature is now active and will automatically track Core Web Vitals and performance metrics when the application is deployed to Vercel.
